{
  "texts": [
    "The generation times are calculated using a single core of an AMD EPYC 7742 CPU and a single NVIDIA RTX 3080 GPU.",
    "The mean and standard deviations are calculated from 10 iterations.",
    "The required time for the jet simulation from the traditional MC simulation is taken from Ref.",
    "ModelHardware Batch Size # of forward calls Time (ms) MC Simulation CPU --46.2 MPGAN CPU 1 1 4.83 ± 0.04 GPU 1 1 3.52 ± 0.22 10 4.88 ± 0.08 1000 51.67 ± 1.47 PC-JeDi CPU 1 1 5.98 ± 0.18 200 1023.91 ± 3.54 GPU 1 1 3.12 ± 0.04 200 498.44 ± 1.86 10 1 3.30 ± 0.12 200 515.76 ± 1.05 1000 1 24.48 ± 0.30 200 4721.58 ± 8.02 Layer-Norm Multi-Headed Attention Layer-Norm Input Point Cloud + Layer-Norm Linear SiLU Layer-Norm Dropout Linear Dense Network + Context Information Attention Network layer of size 256 and the dropout rate is set to 0.1.",
    "For the time embedding layer we use cosine encoding with an output size of M = 16.We use the Adam optimizer [89] with default settings, a batch size of 256, and set the learning rate to ramp up linearly from 0 to 0.0005 over the first 10000 training iterations."
  ]
}